a beautiful memorial piece for my dear friend @fibrous.co in honor of her cat & best friend Luna. drawn years ago by hallie (@she_ceramics), tattooed about a month & a half ago by me. i have been thinking about Luna a lot lately & the time my cat milo and i lived with ellen, luna, phil & hans. it was pretty remarkable that she put up with two new adult cats in her home who liked to steal her food.
i can recall so clearly her piercing eyes, her raspy 2 pack a day meow, and the way she would balance on top of ellen’s knee, flicking her tail as she studied my cat milo lounging across the room. now is the time of day she would be coming inside from her ritualistic morning bask in the sun. we miss you luna 💫

i am out sick the last few days with this cold that is going around austin (no c0vid thankfully). so i will share some tattoos from my last flash day at @nogoodtattoo !
-
you may have noticed that the artists at no good tend to do a lot of flash days. for many of us, this is because flash days offer an opportunity for clients to get tattoos at a discounted price (usually $120-$180 for my flash days vs the regular appt min of $200) and for us to really grind for a day to make a reliable chunk of income needed for the month. it benefits both artist & client! i have come to really rely on flash days to get some of my bills paid, esp when i get sick and am out of work for a week 😓 so I hope to keep putting out new designs that folks are into :-) thank u if you have ever come out to a flash day! i appreciate you so much!
